                When you access Tamboti, you will first be presented with the search interface. The search interface consists of several parts.
            </para><para><itemizedlist><listitem>Below the Tamboti logo, you will find the buttons for "Login" and "Help" - presumably you are now reading this tutorial because
                        you have clicked the latter one.</listitem><listitem>Below that, you will find a set of tabs. The tabs open by default on Simple Search: the other tabs are Advanced Search, Query
                        History and My List. The functions that these tabs give access twill be explained below; they are similar to functions found in most
                        library catalogues.</listitem><listitem>Below the area controlled by the tabs, you will find a grey vertical column, headed by the Folder View button.</listitem><listitem>To the right of the Folder View button, you will find the found count for the current search and the links for navigating from one group of search hits (composed of ten records) to another group.</listitem></itemizedlist></para><para><graphic fileref="images/walk-through.04.png" align="center" valign="middle"/></para></chapter></book>